HEADWORD: Sorosis
<hw>So*ro"sis</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ a
heap.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A fleshy fruit formed by the
consolidation of many flowers with their receptacles, ovaries, etc., as
the breadfruit, mulberry, and pineapple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

